hadiths[2]{hadithnumber,text,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
190,"“Anas ibn Malik brought out to us a wooden drinking vessel, roughly clamped with iron, then he said: ‘O Ihabit, this is the drinking vessel of Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless\nhim and give him peace)'!”",,,48905,"Thabit said:",Chapter 28
191,"""I had given Allah’s Messenger (Allah bless him and give him peace) every kind of beverage to drink using this vessel: water, date juice, honey and milk.”",,,48906,"Anas said:",Chapter 28
